notes: Amiss (134 balls, 161 minutes, 9 fours) completed the first century at this level off 130 balls in the 46th over. He shared the first hundred partnership with Fletcher, the pair addind 125 in 86 minutes (26.4 overs)

milestones.description: Dennis Amiss's 103 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for ENG), surpassing John Edrich's 82
Ian Chappell has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, breaking John Edrich's record
Ian Chappell has become the top scorer in ODIs with 113 runs, going past John Edrich's 82
Dennis Amiss's 103 is the highest individual score in ODIs, surpassing John Edrich's 82
This is the highest match aggregate (448) involving teams England & Australia in ODIs
Dennis Amiss has become the top scorer for ENG in ODIs with 103 runs, going past John Edrich's 82
Dennis Amiss has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (36) in an innings in ODIs for ENG, going past John Edrich's 16
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for ENG, going past Colin Cowdrey
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
England's 226 is the highest total in ODIs, surpassing Australia's 191
Dennis Amiss has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (36) in an innings in ODIs, going past Ian Chappell's 26
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2), going past Greg Chappell
Dennis Amiss and Fletcher's 125-run partnership is ENG's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between Fletcher and John Edrich
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 48-run partnership is the highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 21 between John Edrich and Geoff Boycott
Dennis Amiss and Fletcher's 125-run partnership is the highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between John Edrich and Fletcher
Paul Sheahan and Ross Edwards's 11-run partnership is the highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Ian Chappell and Greg Chappell
Rod Marsh and Ross Edwards's 35-run partnership is the highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between John Edrich and Alan Knott
Mallett and Ross Edwards's 17-run partnership is the highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 15 between John Snow and Alan Knott
Dennis Amiss and Fletcher's 125-run partnership is the highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between Doug Walters and Ian Chappell
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 48-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 21 between John Edrich and Geoff Boycott
Dennis Amiss and Fletcher's 125-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between John Edrich and Fletcher
Dennis Amiss and Hampshire's 41-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 20 between John Edrich and Hampshire
D'Oliveira and Hampshire's 11-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between Colin Cowdrey and John Edrich
Ian Chappell and Stackpole's 62-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 32 between Bill Lawry and Ian Chappell
Paul Sheahan and Ross Edwards's 11-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 7 between Ian Chappell and Greg Chappell

stories.title: ENGLAND v. AUSTRALIA
stories.subTitle: (First One-Day Match)
stories.summary: Amiss and Fletcher, with a daring second-wicket partnership of 125 in eighty-six minutes, swept England to a comfortable victory with 5.5 overs to spare
